					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/aimengie" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4328035); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=4328035&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610226578" alt="AimEngie" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=4328035)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/aimengie" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4328035); return false;" >AimEngie</a></span> <span class="odate time_1544494821 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">11 Dec 2018 02:20</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4082481">
									

<p>I'm not sure if this may help but back when I was getting tested for ADD (plus a few other odds and ends) I was given some kind of targeted test. I believe it was similar to the component score mentioned above. It independently touched on my linguistics, mathematical prowess, problem solving, attention span, and spatial reasoning. Then it put me on a bell curve similar to a standard IQ test.<br />
Might be useful in describing a SCP's type of intelligence. For instance conventionally my IQ is about 125. It is largely brought down by a 73 in attention span (gotta love that distractability) and balanced by a 145 in problem solving (very good with riddles and pattern recognition). Most people are a conglomerate abilities so this could help make a better psychological profile.<br />
This way you could address the talents of various sentient entities. Say a multi-dimensional entity is tested at a 100 IQ but is brought down by a language barrier and excels in spatial awareness. Or a humanoid who never received a formal education scores below average but only because they are inexperienced with math. In scenarios similar to these they could help with immersion/characterization.</p>

							</div>

								
					
